5|$|Stainless steel was {{discovered}} by Harry Brearley in 1912, at the Brown Firth Laboratories in Sheffield. His successor as manager at Brown Firth, Dr William Hatfield, continued Brealey's work. In 1924 he patented '18-8 stainless steel', which to <b>this</b> <b>day</b> <b>is</b> probably the most common alloy of this type.|$|E
5|$|The Civil Service Day {{is celebrated}} on 21 April every year. The purpose for <b>this</b> <b>day</b> <b>is</b> to rededicate and recommit {{themselves}} {{to the cause of}} the people. It is observed by all Civil Services. This day gives civil servants the opportunity for introspection and thinking about future strategies to deal with the challenges being posed by the changing times.|$|E
